place.name: CHAPEL HILL
place.gazetteerText: CHAPEL-HILL, a chapelry in Swineshead parish, Lincoln; near the Lincoln and Boston railway, 3 miles from Coningsby. It has a post office under Boston. Statistics, with the parish. The living is a p. curacy in the diocese of Lincoln. Value, £47. Patron, the Vicar of Swineshead. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
